In[11]:
def age_raiting_transforming(data):
    rating = data['rating']
    if rating == 'EC' or rating == 'K-A' or rating == 'E':
        return '1'
    elif rating == 'E10+':
        return '2'
    elif rating == 'T':
        return '3'
    elif rating == 'M' or rating == 'AO':
        return '4'
    return None

data['rating'] = data.apply(age_raiting_transforming, axis=1)
data['rating'] = data['rating'].astype('float')

In[22]:
def get_life_circle(data):

    platform_circle = data.groupby('platform', as_index=False) \
                          .agg({'year_of_release': 'min'}) \
                          .merge(data.groupby('platform', as_index=False) \
                                     .agg({'year_of_release': 'max'}), on='platform') \
                          .merge(data.groupby(['platform', 'year_of_release'], as_index=False) \
                                     .agg({'sales': 'sum'}) \
                                     #   + ->  
                                     .groupby(['platform'], as_index=False) \
                                     .agg({'sales': 'max'}) \
                                     #    ->                               
                                     .merge(data.groupby(['platform', 'year_of_release'], as_index=False) \
                                                .agg({'sales': 'sum'}),
                                            on=['sales', 'platform'], how='left'),
                                     on='platform') \
                          .rename(columns={'year_of_release_x': 'was_born',
                                             'year_of_release_y': 'died',
                                             'year_of_release': 'peak'}) \
                          .drop('sales', axis=1)
    
    platform_circle['lifetime'] = platform_circle['died'] - platform_circle['was_born']
    platform_circle['to_peak'] = platform_circle['peak'] - platform_circle['was_born']
    platform_circle['to_death'] = platform_circle['died'] - platform_circle['peak']

    platform_circle_values = platform_circle[['lifetime', 'to_peak', 'to_death']].describe().round(1)
    platform_circle = platform_circle.append(platform_circle_values)
    
    return platform_circle

def draw_plot(d):
    genre_sales = d.pivot_table(index='year_of_release',
                                columns='genre',
                                values='sales',
                                aggfunc='sum')
    genre_sales['sum'] = genre_sales.sum(axis=1)

    for index in genre_sales.index:
        genre_sales.loc[index] = genre_sales.loc[index] / genre_sales.loc[index, 'sum'] * 100
    genre_sales = genre_sales.drop(columns='sum')

    genre_sales.plot(figsize=(16, 9),
                     grid=True,
                     title='     ',
                     xlabel='  ',
                     ylabel='  (%)',
                     xticks=np.arange(d['year_of_release'].min(), d['year_of_release'].max() + 1),
                     rot= 45 if d['year_of_release'].max() - d['year_of_release'].min() > 10 else 0)

In[40]:
def get_region_sales(data, region):
    col = region + '_sales'
    
    sales_by_platform = data.groupby('platform', as_index=False) \
                            .agg({col: 'sum'}) \
                            .sort_values(by=col, ascending=False) \
                            .rename(columns={'platform': region + '_top_p', col: col + '_p'}) \
                            .reset_index(drop=True) \
                            .head(5)
    
    sales_by_genre = data.groupby('genre', as_index=False) \
                         .agg({col: 'sum'}) \
                         .sort_values(by=col, ascending=False) \
                         .rename(columns={'genre': region + '_top_g', col: col + '_g'}) \
                         .reset_index(drop=True) \
                         .head(5)
    
    region_sales = sales_by_platform.merge(sales_by_genre, left_index=True, right_index=True)
    
    return region_sales

def t_test(data_1, data_2, equal_var):

    r = st.ttest_ind(data_1, data_2, equal_var=equal_var)
    alpha = 0.05
    text = """   {0:.5f}.
    : {1:.5f}%.""" \
             .format(abs(r[0]), r.pvalue * 100)
    print(text)
    if r.pvalue < alpha:
        print('  .')
    else:
        print('    .')
